question about magus the future magic it says that you may play the top card of your library does that mean that you still have to pay its casting cost like as if it were in your hand or may you just play it w o casting cost and another question about barbed shockers if lets say i have barbed shockers that dealt combat damage to the opponent does that mean that he she has to discard his her hand and draw the same amount of cards twice or just once re magus of the future the only thing that it allows you to do is play the top card of your library normally you can only play cards from your hand per game rules magus of the future alters that rule however it doesn't modify the process for playing a card so you still have to pay for the card when you play it only effects that specifically say play without paying the mana cost or some such make it so that you don't have to pay for the card you can look up related rulings involving the card future sight re barbed shockers yes the opponent will have to discard his her hand twice and draw that many cards twice each barbed shocker has a separate triggered ability and they resolve one at a time if your opponent has four cards in hand he will have to discard those draw four cards then discard those and draw four more some good with megrim Poker jargon Seventh Sea (collectible card game) Magic: The Gathering Legend of the Five Rings Collectible Card Game Blackjack Draw poker Canasta Mao (game) Battle City (Yu-Gi-Oh!) Doomtown Betting (poker) Stud poker Urza's Destiny Community card poker Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game VS System Star Trek Customizable Card Game President (game) Negima Chrono Trigger UNO (game) Mirrodin Cheating in poker Contract bridge Mercadian Masques (Magic: The Gathering) Power Nine Gin rummy Virtual Realm RuneScape Sheepshead Priest (World of Warcraft) Cribbage Tempest (Magic: The Gathering) Skat Ra (board game) Stronghold (Magic: The Gathering) Collectible card game Five-card draw Consensus decision-making Mem